select1.hint: Standard Operating Conditions: - Less than 120m height (400ft). - Greater than 5.5km from the nearest airfield. - More than 30m from any person not associated with the flight . - Approval from CASA required to fly in controlled airspace, prohibited area or restricted area. - Select a location for take-off and landing. This location should be at least 10m radius with no obstructions. - Do NOT fly above or near populated places or large crowds. - Fly in moderate weather conditions with temperatures between 0Â° to 40Â°C. - DO NOT fly when the wind speeds exceed 29kph (16 Knots).

Pre flight check: - Visually inspect the DJI Phantom 4 Pro for damage or wear paying attention to the frame, motors, gimbal, lights, propellers and undercarriage. - Ensure that a Micro SD card is properly inserted into the UAV body. - Ensure that the handset and DJI intelligent batteries are fully charged. - Ensure that the propellers are properly attached and spin freely.

The Remote Pilot is to complete an on-site briefing to all crew members and observers, outlining but not limited to: - The mission - Each crew member's duties. - Hazards and potential hazards. - Communication strategies. - Emergency landing areas. - Safe zones. - What to do in am emergency. - Location of emergency contact numbers.

input.hint: You must complete a risk assessment and all pre flight checks to fly.
